“Today, the young doctors feel free to say, ‘I’m terrified, but I’m going to do it anyway.’ That’s courage.
“You can save lives.
And when you can’t save lives you can be in the darkness with patients even if there is nothing to offer.
But when you look at what’s happening across the country right now, you see the benefits of their tough training.
When hiring doctors for his hospital in the African jungle, he wrote, he never hired anyone who thought he was doing something grand and heroic.